Package: GeneCardAnalysis
Title: Interactive RT-qPCR Data Analysis and Visualisation
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: c(
    person("Sebastiano", "Di Bella", role = c("aut", "cre"),
           email = "sebastiano.dibella@unipa.it",
           comment = c(ORCID = "0000-0001-7161-303X")),
    person("Francesco", "Orilio", role = "aut",
		email = "francesco.orilio@unipa.it")
  )
Description: A Shiny web application for reproducible analysis and visualisation
    of RT-qPCR data. Implements the delta-CT normalisation method
    (Livak & Schmittgen, 2001 <doi:10.1006/meth.2001.1262>) to compute
    normalised expression values (2^(-deltaCT)), log2 fold-changes relative
    to a user-defined reference condition, and per-gene z-scores on the log2
    scale. Results are visualised as publication-ready heatmaps (via
    ComplexHeatmap) and ranked bar charts. Interactive controls allow the user
    to configure clustering, column ordering, and colour palettes. Experimental
    comparisons are defined via a YAML configuration file or through an in-app
    form. All outputs can be exported as PNG, PDF, Excel, and ZIP archives.
